+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015a78AVn1wf7qyKAsZhn4f4","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Phase 11: Middleware Pipeline\n     2→\n     3→Add a middleware system that can intercept and transform tasks as they are processed.\n     4→\n     5→## Requirements\n     6→\n     7→- Middleware functions can be registered per queue.\n     8→- When a task is processed, it passes through all registered middleware in order before reaching the final handler.\n     9→- Each middleware receives the task and a \"next\" function. Calling \"next\" passes control to the next middleware (or the handler).\n    10→- If a middleware does NOT call \"next\", the task processing is skipped.\n    11→- Middleware can modify the task (e.g., adding metadata or transforming the payload).\n    12→- If a middleware throws an error, the task should be marked as failed.\n    13→- A processing function/handler can be registered per queue. It is invoked after all middleware have run.\n    14→- Each queue has its own independent middleware stack.\n    15→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01VMsX3E5e7Jzv5J6haUBssF","session_id":"77620456-c1eb-42d4-a9de-c5173acf4f37","uuid":"2fd506da-dbc7-42a9-b0dd-1e32c470db92"}
